==English==

===Etymology===
From the ''[Bible]'' "Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither '''cast ye your pearls before swine''', lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you." - [[KJV]], ''Matthew 7:6''
[http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_%28World_English%29/Matthew#Chapter_7 Matthew 7:6]

===Phrase===
'''[[cast]] [[pearl]]s [[before]] [[swine]]'''

# {{idiom}} To give things of value to those who will not understand or appreciate it.

